AllLife Credit Card Customer Segmentation - Project¶

Background:¶

AllLife Bank wants to focus on its credit card customer base in the next financial year. They have been advised by their marketing research team, that the penetration in the market can be improved. Based on this input, the Marketing team proposes to run personalised campaigns to target new customers as well as upsell to existing customers. Another insight from the market research was that the customers perceive the support services of the back poorly. Based on this, the Operations team wants to upgrade the service delivery model, to ensure that customers queries are resolved faster. Head of Marketing and Head of Delivery both decide to reach out to the Data Science team for help.

Objective:¶

To identify different segments in the existing customer based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank.

Key Questions:¶

  • How many different segments of customers are there?
  • How are these segments different from each other?
  • What are your recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers?

Data Description:¶

Data is of various customers of a bank with their credit limit, the total number of credit cards the customer has, and different channels through which customer has contacted the bank for any queries, different channels include visiting the bank, online and through a call.

  • Customer key - Identifier for the customer
  • Average Credit Limit - Average credit limit across all the credit cards
  • Total credit cards - Total number of credit cards
  • Total visits bank - Total number of bank visits
  • Total visits online - total number of online visits
  • Total calls made - Total number of calls made by the customer

Distortion¶

  • Defined as "the sum of the squared differences between the observations and the correspond centroid". However, it is implemented as the sum of the (unsquared) differences.
  • How far your point is to your centroid.
  • Low is better
In [16]:
clusters = range(1,9)
meanDistortions = []

for k in clusters:
    model = KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(subset_scaled_df)
    prediction = model.predict(subset_scaled_df)
    distortion = sum(np.min(cdist(subset_scaled_df, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / subset_scaled_df.shape[0]
                           
    meanDistortions.append(distortion)

    print('Number of Clusters:', k, '\tAverage Distortion:', distortion)

plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average Distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method', fontsize=20)

Lets us check sihoutte score¶

silhouette_score (sklearn.metrics) for the data set is used for measuring the mean of the Sihouette Coefficient for each sample belonging to different clusters.

Sihouette Coefficient or sihoutte score is a metric used to calculate the goodness of a clustering technique. Its value ranges from -1 to 1.

  • 1: means the clusters are well apart from each other and clearly distiguished.
  • 0: means clusters are indifferent, or we can say that the distance between clusters is not significant.
  • -1: means clusters are assigned in the wrong way.
In [17]:
sil_score = []
cluster_list = list(range(2,10))
for n_clusters in cluster_list:
    clusterer = KMeans(n_clusters = n_clusters)
    preds = clusterer.fit_predict(subset_scaled_df)
    score = silhouette_score(subset_scaled_df, preds)
    sil_score.append(score)
    print('For n_clusters ={}, silhouette score is {})'.format(n_clusters, score))

Find out the linkage matrix¶

  • cophenet index is a measure of the correlation between the distance of points in feature space and distance on dendrogram.
  • closer it is to 1, the better is the clustering.

- Ward as linkage metric and Eucledian as distance.¶

In [30]:
from scipy.cluster.hierarchy import dendrogram, linkage,cophenet
Z_Ward = linkage(X_std, 'ward', metric ='euclidean')
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist # Pairwise distribution between data points
C, coph_dists = cophenet(Z_Ward, pdist(X_std))
C

0.7415156284827493

Analysis and Insight¶

By looking at boxplot in AgglomerativeClustering

  • Cluster 0:

    • Avg_Credit_Limit has the highest value at 100,000. Majority of customer have values around 15,000 to 50,000.
    • Total_Credit_Cards is about 7 as highest value and lowest 2. Majority of customer in this cluster between 4-6
    • Total_visits_bank is high 5 and min is 1
    • Total_visits_online is low
    • Total_calls_made is medium

  • Cluster 1:

    • Avg_Credit_limit is high
    • Total_Credit_Cards also high of majority of customers
    • Total_visit_bank is low 0-1
    • Total_visit_online is high
    • Total_calls_made is low. it is just truth because they visit online a lot.

  • Cluster 2:

    • Avg_Credit_limit is low
    • Total_Credit_Cards is also low than others
    • Total_visit_bank is kind of medium
    • Total_visit_line is also kind of medium between 1-5
    • Total_calls_made is high

Business Recommendation¶

  • Cluster 1: is the best customer segment for the Bank. They have high value of total credit cards and average credit limit. They use a lot of online banking which is good for bank saving human services and time. Markerting team should target more on this type of customer.

  • Cluster 2: is not good new customer segment and need some improvement. They have low total number of credit cards and average credit limit, but total visit bank medium and total call made a lot. This show us that some improvement need to be done with customer support service. Why customer in this segement use customer support service a lot, but not much benefit to the business or Bank (low credit cards and average credit limit)?

  • Cluster 0: I would say it is a medium customer segment, it is also good. They have medium of average credit limit and total credit cards. They also use a lot of customer support by go visit the Bank directly instead of online banking and call.

Inclusion: As a data scientis of the Bank, I would suggest or recommend Head of Delivery Team to revisit with customer support team, especially with call center because based on our anlysis on the data show us that Bank is having poor service with customer support call center.
